Use code with caution.Next Steps to get it running:Save the File: Copy the block above, open your .env file, replace your old placeholder lines, and save it.Restart Vite: In your terminal, stop your running website server (Ctrl + C) and start it again with npm run dev (or your framework's start command) so it loads the new configuration.Double-Check Supabase Backend: Make sure you have also gone into your Supabase Dashboard (under Edge Functions ➔ Secrets) and added RAZORPAY_KEY_ID with rzp_live_TEcApCcyhTptHt along with its matching RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET.Once you restart your development server and try checking out, does the 401 Unauthorized error disappear from your dashboard invocations history?

# =====================================================================
# RAZORPAY PAYMENT GATEWAY
# Frontend only exposes the KEY_ID (public, used by checkout.js)
# KEY_SECRET is strictly backend-only and set as Supabase secrets
# =====================================================================
VITE_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_live_TEcApCcyhTptHt

# =====================================================================
# SUPABASE EDGE FUNCTIONS - SECRETS (DO NOT ADD HERE)
# These are NOT read by the Vite frontend — set them ONLY as Supabase
# Edge Function secrets in the dashboard, e.g.:
#   Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets
#   Add:
#     RAZORPAY_KEY_ID = rzp_live_TEcApCcyhTptHt
#     RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET = your-secret
#
# SUPABASE_URL / SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY / SUPABASE_ANON_KEY are
# provided automatically by the Supabase Edge Runtime and don't need
# to be set manually.
# =====================================================================

# supabase/functions/send-email (SMTP)
SMTP_HOST=
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=
SMTP_PASS=
SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@praxisgroup.online
SMTP_FROM_NAME=Praxis Group

# supabase/functions/send-email (Resend fallback, optional)
RESEND_API_KEY=
